Metatranscriptome analysis of Eulimnogammarus verrucosus microbiome

Workflow

Data preprocessing

The data were prepared as follows: (1) raw data were cleared from adapters, (2) from rRNA before project start.

The number of reads for each samples is given below.

BBDuk k-mers analysis

For analysis we used Silva DB (reference_SILVADB.fasta):

  • Vortivella_SILVADB.fasta

  • Peritrichia_SILVADB.fasta

  • Ciliophora_SILVADB.fasta

  • Eulimnogammarus_verrucosus_SILVADB.fasta

bbduk.sh -Xmx1g -in1=reads_R1.fastq.gz -in2=reads_R2.fastq.gz ref=reference_SILVADB.fasta k=50 hdist=0 outm=match_reads.fq out=no_match.fq stats=sample.stats.txt threads=2

We calculated the ratio iliate reads / E. verrucosus reads

iliate Eve_B6 F-100-BK-1
Vorticella 1.0106 1.0570
Peritrichia 1.0147 1.0690
Ciliophora 1.0202 1.0961

BBDuk clear from muscle

Used an assembly of muscle of Eulimnogammarus verrucosus to clean microbiome.

bbduk.sh -Xmx2g -in1=reads_R1.fastq.gz -in2=reads_R2.fastq.gz ref=EveNEB_muscle.filtered.fasta -out1=reads_womuscleR1.fq -out2=reads_womuscleR2.fq k=50 hdist=0 stats=sample.stats.txt threads=2

Reads left after cleaning:

Rcorrector correcting data

perl run_rcorrector.pl -1 /path/to/reads_womuscleR1.fq -2 /path/to/reads_womuscleR2.fq -t 2

Reads left after correction:

Assembly

MEGAHIT

time megahit -1 reads_womuscleR1.cor.fq -2 reads_womuscleR2.cor.fq --memory 8e9 --num-cpu-threads 2 --out-prefix target --out-dir ./output_directory -f

rnaSPAdes

Samples differ in chain specificity:

./rnaspades.py -1 /path/to/EveB6_womuscleR1.cor.fq -2 /path/to/EveB6_womuscleR2.cor.fq -t 4 -m 50 -o /path/to/data_for_assembly/EveB6_rnasp --ss fr
./rnaspades.py -1 /path/to/F100-BK1_womuscleR1.cor.fq -2 /path/to/F100-BK1_womuscleR2.cor.fq -t 4 -m 50 -o /path/to/F100-BK1_rnasp --ss rf

Trinity

./Trinity --left /path/to/EveB6_womuscleR1.cor.fq --right /path/to/EveB6_womuscleR2.cor.fq --SS_lib_type FR --seqType fq --max_memory 50G --CPU 4 --output /path/to/EveB6_trinity
./Trinity --left /path/to/F100-BK1_womuscleR1.cor.fq --right /path/to/F100-BK1_womuscleR2.cor.fq --SS_lib_type RF --seqType fq --max_memory 50G --CPU 4 --output /path/to/F100_BK1_trinity

Assembly results

Total contigs count:

QC assembly TransRate

transrate --assembly target_assembly.fa

Contig length distribution:

Less than 200 bp contigs are mostly found in the rnaSPAdes assembly.

ORF contigs number:

QC assembly BUSCO

Databases were pre-downloaded. The launch was carried out using a script:

python3 busco_run.py

Bowtie 2

A Bowtie 2 was used to estimate the amount of aligned reads.

bowtie2-build target_assembly
bowtie2 -p 10 -q --no-unal -k 20 -x target_assembly -1 reads_womuscleR1.cor.fq -2 reads_womuscleR2.cor.fq 2>align.stats.target.txt > logs.txt

CD-HIT correction

./cd-hit-est -i target_assembly.fasta -o target_assembly_clear -c 0.95 -n 8

QC after correction: TransRate

Total contigs count:

QC after correction: BUSCO

Analysis of taxonomy

Used the base UniProtKB_Swiss-Prot:

mmseqs databases UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot UniProtKB_Swiss-ProtDB tmp

Prepare the bases:

mmseqs createdb target_assembly.fasta
mmseqs createdb UniProtKB_Swiss-Prot UniProtKB_Swiss-ProtDB

Prepare annotation base:

mmseqs createtaxdb UniProtKB_Swiss-ProtDB tmp

Building a taxonomy (-s - sensivity, use 2, 6, 7.5, final results on -s 7.5):

mmseqs taxonomy target_assembly UniProtKB_Swiss-ProtDB lca_result tmp -s X

Generate reports:

# Pavian
mmseqs taxonomyreport UniProtKB_Swiss-ProtDB lca_result taxonomyResult_report
# Krona
mmseqs taxonomyreport UniProtKB_Swiss-ProtDB lca_result report.html --report-mode 1

From the Pavian report take data on the distribution of taxa:
